// Title: React2Shell C2 and Metadata Exfiltration Detection
// Product: Microsoft Defender for Endpoint – Advanced Hunting
// ATT&CK: T1071.001 (Application Layer Protocol: Web Protocols), T1567.002 (Exfiltration Over Web Services), T1105 (Ingress Tool Transfer)
// Data Sources: DeviceNetworkEvents
// Description: Flags outbound network connections from endpoints or servers to known command‑and‑control infrastructure and metadata endpoints used in the React2Shell campaign.  Observed malicious activity includes calls to Cloudflare tunnels (`trycloudflare.com`), the `C3pool` mining pool, malicious IP addresses (206.237.3.150, 45.77.33.136, 143.198.92.82, 183.6.80.214) and the cloud metadata endpoint 169.254.169.254【677298509385333†L1330-L1360】【894970168289148†L246-L354】.  Such connections may indicate post‑exploitation data exfiltration or beaconing.
// Author: Ahsan M.

let c2IPs = dynamic(["206.237.3.150", "45.77.33.136", "143.198.92.82", "183.6.80.214"]);
let c2Domains = dynamic(["trycloudflare.com", "c3pool", "api.cleanmasters.store"]);
DeviceNetworkEvents
| where Timestamp > ago(14d)
| where RemoteIP in (c2IPs) 
       or RemoteUrl has_any (c2Domains)
       or RemoteIP == "169.254.169.254"
| project Timestamp, DeviceName, InitiatingProcessFileName, InitiatingProcessCommandLine,
    RemoteIP, RemotePort, RemoteUrl, Protocol, LocalIP, LocalPort

// Tuning: maintain an allowlist of legitimate services that use Cloudflare tunnels or connect to metadata endpoints.  Many legitimate applications may query `169.254.169.254` for cloud instance metadata; consider adding conditions such as user context (e.g., service accounts) or combining with process indicators (Node/Bun).  Remove internal IP ranges if your environment uses NAT.

// Validation: simulate C2 connections by performing a DNS lookup or HTTP request to `trycloudflare.com` or a test IP from a lab system and confirm the query surfaces the event.  For metadata calls, run `curl http://169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data/` from a test VM and ensure the detection triggers.

// MITRE Mapping:
//  - T1071.001 – Application Layer Protocol: Web Protocols (HTTP/S C2 communications)
//  - T1567.002 – Exfiltration Over Web Services (exfiltration via cloud metadata services and public web services)
//  - T1105 – Ingress Tool Transfer (download of payloads from C2)

// Recommended Alert Rule Settings:
//  - Schedule: every 15 minutes
//  - Lookup window: 1 hour
//  - Threshold: >0 results
//  - Severity: Medium (raise to High if combined with suspicious process indicators)
//  - Entity mappings: DeviceName (hostname), RemoteIP (IP), InitiatingProcessFileName (process)
